<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880722-0035 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Cablevision Industries Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><IN> TNM TEL </IN><TEXT>   Cablevision Industries Corp., Liberty, N.Y., agreed definitively to acquire Wometco Cable TV Inc., whose stockholders include affiliates and associates of Fort Worth, Texas-based Robert M. Bass Group.    Terms weren't disclosed, but a source close to the transaction, to be completed Dec. 1, put the total value at about $720 million, including assumption of almost $700 million of debt with the balance to be paid in Cablevision stock.    Cablevision will gain about 308,500 additional cable subscribers in North Carolina, South Carolina, Oklahoma, Louisiana, West Virginia, Georgia and Alabama.    Cablevision and its affiliates operate systems serving more than 540,000 subscribers in New York, Pennsylvania, Massachusetts, Florida, Virginia, Tennessee, Michigan and California.    A spokesman for the Bass group couldn't be reached for comment. </TEXT></DOC>